Labour Minister Mildred Oliphant, has on Friday confirmed that three unions have agreed on the proposed wage settlement. “I am pleased that finally the unions and employees have reached an agreement on the wage offer. I want to thank the African National Congress (ANC) for the clear guidance it has offered to me,” Mildred said. The minister was speaking at the press briefing where she and other union’s representatives were giving feedback of the post negotiations. She revealed that only three unions signed the agreement with employers, adding that NUMSA was still in caucus with employers. “Three unions have signed as we speak and NUMSA is still negotiating at the moment,” the minister added. Meanwhile, union representative, told journalist that they will continue engages with employers going forward. TNA Reporter